There is, however, in this conception left open the possibility of
securing a brief visit from them for purposes that are supposed to serve
the living. How easily out of this could develop the idea and practice
of necromancy!

On the other hand one may support with abundant evidence the thesis that
there is a quite general consensus to the effect that it is unseemly for
departed spirits to inhabit the land where the living pass their earthly
existence. It is widely believed that ghosts have their own land whither
living mortals may not go, whence, also, spirits may not

